,Recommended,218510,12032605,"Posted: 9 September, 2014",all,EsotericMoniker,"While clearly inspired by Galcon, Planet's Under Attack adds some much needed depth to the formula. Your planets produce units as in Galcon but attacking requires money. While you attack you don't generate money. Also, the closer you are to your money cap, the more powerful your ships are. Also, sending ships to defend a planet you already control costs nothing. This creates a wonderful risk/reward balance where you want to commit to attacks you can win, and only with just enough ships to take it.Now add in 2 other races that each have modified rules for production (think the races in Starcraft 2 and how they are similar but unique in how they go about it) and you have not only a fine single player game but a great multiplayer setup. The campaign unfortunately only features the humans.If you liked Eufloria, Mushroom Wars, or Blue Libra 2, there's definitely something new to like here."
